      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"9. PETITE ANGE turned in a nice effort to score two runs ago at this track. Couldn't follow that up last time out when fifth over 1308m at this track, beaten 7 lengths. Enjoys a drop in grade so she is a major player. 3. CHOKECHERY SHARI progressed nicely last time out when she made late ground to finish just 1.3 lengths from the winner in second over 1207m at this track. Well placed and there is no reason she cannot find winning ways. 1. LOTSA STEEL wasn't far away last time out, finishing fourth over 1106m at this track (Dirt) when she was always up in the leading division. The extra journey should play into her hands. Poses a genuine threat. 6. RABBLE is close to breaking through after two consecutive placings, the latest coming when third over 1106m at this track (Dirt). Well placed and there is no reason she cannot find winning ways.\",\"runners\":[9,3,1,6],\"exclusive\":false}",
